# Proposal Writer — audio-software-engineer-needed-for

Three deliverables written to `proposal/`, styled with the Sanctuary demo's worship stage-console palette (bg #0C0C0F, amber #F59E0B accent, surface hierarchy, Inter + JetBrains Mono). Not michaelwegter.com's look.

## Files written

- `proposal/cover-letter.md` — In Michael's voice per `reference/brand-voice.md`. Leads with the live demo link, then answers all four application questions explicitly and concretely. Structure: hook (their problem + outcome), demo paragraph, engagement approach, then the four Q&A blocks with honest specific answers. No em/en dashes (verified, 0 matches).
- `proposal/one-pager.html` — Self-contained dark worship-console HTML one-pager (amber/white/muted palette, Inter + JetBrains Mono, Google Fonts CDN). Sections: eyebrow + name header, demo hero with live screenshot and CTA button, 9-pain-point coverage grid (all green checkmarks), three-up screenshot strip, callout quote, four credential cards (music degree, DJ, MIDI bridge, engineering career), tech stack tag cloud (audio-relevant highlighted in amber), four-step audit approach, footer CTA linking both the demo and the work-samples route. No em/en dashes (verified, 0 matches).
- `proposal/make_deck.py` — python-pptx generator. 8-slide 16:9 deck, same dark/amber palette.
- `proposal/deck.pptx` — Generated successfully (`python3 make_deck.py`). 8 slides, 661 KB.

